We approached this problem by creating all possible pairs of amplicons and then comparing them based off the number of distinguishable strains metric. The best amplicon pairs were chosen to have the highest number of distinguishable strains. The amplicon pairs are printed as sets, with all of the first amplicon printed before all of the second amplicon.

Right primer for the first amplicon in the #1 amplicon pair:GCAGCGACCATTTCTGGAG
Left primer for the second amplicon in the #1 amplicon pair:GATGCGCTGATCATTTACGA
Right primer for the second amplicon in the #1 amplicon pair:AAGGTCGGATGCAAACTGAG
